    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to observe the 12CO (6-5) line wing and the 430 micron continuum emission towards the hot molecular core SMA1 in the high-mass star forming region G19.61-0.23 where gas infall onto a rotating-core and jet system has been detected by our SMA observations. The CO (6-5) observations will detect a jet-like outflow, hence yielding a conclusive evidence for the interpretation. The 430 micron image will be used not only to measure amount of the circumstellar materials, but also to identify possible "companions" around SMA1. All the information derived from the 1.8-hours Band 9 observations will allow us to establish a benchmark for testing the controversy between "monolithic accretion" vs. "competitive accretion" scenarios in high-mass star formation process.
</prp:abstract>
